'''Abdallah Mousa Musallam Nasib''' ({{langx|ar|عَبْد الله مُوسَى مُسْلِم نَصِيب}}; born 25 February 1994) is a Jordanian professional footballer who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Iraq Stars League]] club [[Al-Zawraa SC|Al-Zawraa]], on loan from [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]], and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].

==Club career==
Nasib began his senior career with the Jordanian club [[That Ras SC|That Ras]] in 2016. The following season in 2017, he moved to [[Al-Ramtha SC|Al-Ramtha]] where he stayed for three seasons. On 29 December 2019 he signed with [[Al-Wehdat SC|Al-Wehdat]], where he helped them win the [[2020 Jordanian Pro League]] and [[Jordan Super Cup|2021 Jordan Super Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ammonnews.net/article/507792|title=صحيفة عمون : الوحدات يتعاقد مع اللاعب عبدالله نصيب|website=وكالة عمون الاخبارية}}</ref> On 7 January 2022, he moved to Egypt with [[Al Ittihad Alexandria Club|Al Ittihad]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filgoal.com/articles/425918|title=مصيلحي يعلن عبر في الجول موعد انضمام نصيب وشبانة لتدريبات الاتحاد|first=هاني|last=العوضي|date=January 7, 2022|website=FilGoal.com}}</ref> He returned to Jordan with [[Al-Hussein SC (Irbid)|Al-Hussein]] on 5 July 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1252343|title=رسميا.. الحسين اربد يعلن تعاقده مع ديارا|date=July 5, 2023|website=كووورة}}</ref> On 7 August 2025, Nasib moved to Iraq to join [[Al-Zawraa SC|Al-Zawraa]] for a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=نادي الحسين يعلن إعارة عبدالله نصيب إلى الزوراء العراقي |url=https://royanews.tv/news/355864 |website=royanews.tv |publisher=Roya News |access-date=7 August 2025 |language=Arabic |date=7 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Nasib was first called up to the senior [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]] in a friendly 2–0 loss to [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] on 4 September 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/matches/report/31746/Jordan_Haiti.html|title=Jordan vs. Haiti|first=Benjamin|last=Strack-Zimmermann|website=www.national-football-teams.com}}</ref> He was called up to Jordan for the [[2021 FIFA Arab Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-11-26|title= رسميا.. حمد يعلن قائمة الأردن لكأس العرب |url=https://m.kooora.com/?n=1089782&o=ncjo|access-date=2021-11-26|website=كووورة.كوم|language=ar}}</ref> He was called up to the national team for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khaberni.com/news/17-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%89-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A2%D8%B3-634272|title=موقع خبرني : 17 لاعبا في قائمة النشامى يتواجدون للمرة الأولى بكأس آسيا|website=موقع خبرني}}</ref> where he and the team reached the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup final|final]], losing 3-1 to [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]].

